Tja, so, I flew this today.
First criticism point: We need more beautiful flight logs. Black is boring, pink is not really pink, but salmon-colored.
I wanted to fly since I was a child.
And today it was finally… I flew a plane today. I haven't quite processed it yet.
Data from Flightaware.
I try to drive over again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's still Monday.
It's already clear where the problems lie. It will probably BE VERY difficult to get the medical permission, due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will BE VERY time-consuming and means A LOT of extra work.
This is somewhat discouraging, but it's just another problem that needs to be solved. So far, it seems solvable. It just costs a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what's coming my way.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't give you medical clearance if you're taking medication for it.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I should be able to choose my own tail number for an airplane, then you know for sure it has to be a variant of N1337_, where _ stands for the last available letter.
It makes sense that the sun shines when I'm away, lol. Stupid cow.
I have to get back in the air. And the weather isn't playing along.
